{
    "name": "Fey Friend",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Tactics",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Before Combat </b>The druid casts <i>liveoak </i>every 13 days, and <i>endure elements </i>each morning.<br/><b>During Combat </b>The druid casts <i>stoneskin </i>on her treant and orders it into combat. She wild shapes into a bat and casts <i>cat\u2019s grace </i>and <i>barkskin </i>on herself. She then casts <i>cure </i>spells or spontaneous <i>summon nature\u2019s ally </i>as necessary. If entering melee, she casts <i>protection from energy </i>and <i>greater magic fang</i>, then wild shapes into a treant herself."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "html": "These druids see themselves not as protectors of the forest, but as part of it, like the fey they associate with."
        }
    ],
